comments.body:
Thanks [~cheersyang] for the review.
{quote}
Will this add a lot of if-else? 
{quote}
No, I think we just need to modify some if-else conditions(e.g. "node != null" constrant should be removed from if condition when recording activites in ActivitiesLogger) instead of adding if-else blocks. 
{quote}
Is it possible to make it transparent working for both HB based lookup or multi-node lookup?
{quote}
Sure, we can take CapacityScheduler#allocateContainersToNode as the unified entrance and exit, as described in the second changes to support for scheduler activities——Place the start/finish points of scheduler activities in front of/after the allocation based on single node (input node is a real node) or multiple nodes (input node is ActivitiesManager#MULTI_NODES_AGENT) in CapacityScheduler#allocateContainersToNode instead of CapacityScheduler#nodeUpdate, to expand the applicable scenarios via unified entrance and exit.

